         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_MANUF_FOR_RESEARCH CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
                     <D_EXTREME_URGENCY/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>As per Regulation 32(5) the products involved are manufactured purely for the purposes of research, experimentation, study or development.</P>
                     <P>Furthermore, Coventry has recently received notification that it has been accepted as UK City of Culture 2021. As such there is therefore no time available to run a full OJEU process if a VLR system is to be given potential to be available for demonstration during the year of City of Culture.</P>
                     <P>As such, CCC intent is to award this contract directly to WMG (An Academic Department of Warwick University) after the 10 days standstill period. Unless this VEAT notice alerts other suppliers with the expertise and ability to meet the time schedule for this supply and associated service(s).</P>
                     <P>The provisions of Regulation 99 of the PCR 2015, provides for Grounds of Ineffectiveness — This direct award will be lawful and the first ground does not apply because all of the following apply:</P>
                     <P>a) That CCC considered the award of the contract without prior publication of a contract notice to be permitted by Part.</P>
                     <P>b) That CCC has had published in the OJEU a voluntary transparency notice expressing its intention to enter into a contract and;</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
